Always dump settings file after any run

This is added to ensure that settings can be extended
without interaction by the user.

Add option to have non-square thumbnails and cover images

This commit adds support for non-square coverimages and
thumbnails. Two options have been added (square_thumbnails
and square_coverimage), which are True by default. Since
now the appropriate name for the dim_thumbnail is
dim_max_thumb, the options have been changed and a
DeprecationWarning is thrown when the settings file is
updated.

To correctly deal with EXIF rotation in SmartCrop.js, the
rotated file is saved to a temporary file which is cleaned
up after the crop has been created.

Add settings file validation

HugoPhotoSwipe can't run without a markdown_dir or an output_dir
setting. This commit adds checking to see if the settings file
is okay. Also, the 'init' command didn't need a hps instance, so
this has been removed.
update readme to avoid confusion with photos directories

Fix issues with paths, extensions, date, and url_prefix

Paths on Windows use the backslash but the HTML path should use front
slash. When appending dimensions to the resized image filenames the
extension is now correctly placed only at the end. If no date is defined
in the album.yml then no date is emitted in the frontmatter. url_prefix
was meant to be optional but did not have correct defaults, now fixed.
Don't show progressbar if no items need to be processed

Use cached_property decorator to simplify code

For some properties we already used a simple form of caching
of the return value, to make sure we don't run expensive
code too often. Now, we use an actual cached_property
decorator (taken from Django) to make this process simpler.
In addition, we now also cache opening of the original image
which makes the code run faster because the original image is
only opened once.
